ge_div"><div style="margin:0px;padding:0px;text-align:left;">
To solve this challenge you need some basic knowledge about programming, stegano and logic puzzels. However, you
are lucky, because you don't have to do it all by yourself.
You can use my 'Hint Machine' applet. You simply do that by providing a key to the machine. If the key is right, you
will get a hint you need at that moment.<br /><p>
Especially in the second part of the challenge you will have to find some things. When you find these things a key
will be provided. There is no need to look for the key when you think you found something interesting, because the
key will also be there. Well, you will see it later on :-) It's important to remember that all keys will be numerical.
The 'Hint Machine' assumes that your key is a number of base 10. So, if you may find a key which is not base 10, then
please convert it to base 10 before entering it in the 'Hint Machine'.<br /><p>
Oh, and sometimes you just see a key or a number. Well, you know what to do with it :-) Maybe you need a hint from
the 'Hint Machine' before you can really start...or maybe not...<br />Good luck!<br /><br />

<p class="challenge_1" style="text-align:center;">
<applet code = "LoginSystem.class" width = 300 height = 175></applet>
</p><br />

And here is my 'Hint Machine' applet. You can provide a key anytime you want, but it will only give you a hint when
you enter a valid key. One last note: Don't start a brute force attack on the hint machine, because the applet itself
does not know which keys are valid.<br /> Have fun!<br /><br />

<p class="challenge_1" style="text-align:center;">
<applet code = "HintMachine.class" width = 350 height = 250></applet>
</p><br />
